Hardware Requirements
To reproduce the results or train the Gradient Transformer Self-Attention U-Net model efficiently, the following hardware setup is recommended:
Minimum Requirements:
CPU: Intel Core i5 (8th Gen) or AMD equivalent

RAM: 16 GB

GPU: NVIDIA GTX 1060 (6GB VRAM) or higher

Storage: At least 20 GB free space (for dataset, model checkpoints, and logs)

Recommended Setup (for training on large datasets or faster performance):
CPU: Intel Core i7/i9 or AMD Ryzen 7/9

RAM: 32 GB or more

GPU: NVIDIA RTX 3080 / A100 / V100 with â‰¥10GB VRAM

Storage: SSD with at least 50 GB free space

CUDA: Version 11.3 or later

Operating System: Ubuntu 20.04 / Windows 10 (64-bit)
